Diversity in the workplace is important, because it gives us the ability to solve problems from different viewpoints. 

Consider the history: That Time When Women Stopped Coding

What occurred during the same time as the beginning of the decline of women in computer science?
The beggining of pc's being introduced into households. 

Why does it matter that males had been playing on computers growing up?
They had an earlier introduction into computers, making it easier for them, when they studied, later down the road. 

